Metro Pacific to Buy Hospital Operator for 300 Million Pesos

-- B y   C e c i l i a   Y a p
-- 
2011-10-24T00:38:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-24/metro-pacific-to-buy-hospital-operator-for-300-million-pesos.html
Metro Pacific Investments Corp. (MPI)  said
it agreed to acquire the company that operates Cardinal Santos
Medical Center for 300 million pesos.  Metro Pacific signed an agreement with affiliate Medical
Doctors Inc. to acquire 100 percent of Colinas Verdes Hospital
Managers Corp., it said in a disclosure to the stock exchange
today.  Colinas Verdes, established by Medical Doctors in 2008, has
a 20-year lease agreement with Philippine Realty Corp. to
operate the 237-bed Cardinal Santos Medical Center. Metro
Pacific said that under the transaction it will also assume the
guarantee obligations of Medical Doctors to Philippine Realty.  Medical Doctors, an affiliate of Metro Pacific, owns and
operates the Makati Medical Center.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Cecilia Yap at 
 cyap19@bloomberg.net  